I've raised many, many animals, but the first time I got bunnies, I was 7. I remember the breeder told me to never feed a bunny grapes, but that they could eat grape stems, so all these years, I buy grapes, strip them off the stem give the stem to my bunny and eat the grapes myself. Symbiotic, right? I start watching this and I'm like "NO, WHY ARE YOU GIVING BINI GRAPES!?!?!" Then I start doing research to post a URL supporting me in a comment being all "save Bini from grapes" and realize, bunnies are chill with grapes. Only thing is, don't feed your dog grapes, anyone who reads this. It can cause kidney failure and is almost as bad as feeding them chocolate, but it's not as well known. I've had this confirmed by a vet. Love you Bini!
